description: column constraints, not null, default values, unique constraints, length limits, 
alwaysApply: false
---
## Column Constraints

### NOT NULL

```ruby
# Require value (cannot be NULL)
t.string :title, null: false
t.string :email, null: false
t.integer :user_id, null: false

# Allow NULL (default)
t.string :middle_name  # Can be NULL
```

### Default Values

```ruby
# Set default value
t.boolean :published, default: false
t.integer :views_count, default: 0
t.string :status, default: "draft"
t.datetime :created_at, default: -> { "CURRENT_TIMESTAMP" }

# Array default
t.string :tags, array: true, default: []
```

### Unique Constraints

```ruby
# Single column unique
t.string :email, null: false
add_index :users, :email, unique: true

# Multiple column unique (composite)
add_index :article_tags, [:article_id, :tag_id], unique: true

# Unique with condition
add_index :users, :email, 
          unique: true,
          where: "deleted_at IS NULL"
```

### Length Limits

```ruby
# String length limit
t.string :title, limit: 200
t.string :slug, limit: 100
t.string :phone, limit: 20
```

